<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.10.5/font/bootstrap-icons.css"
    />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/page/download-page.css" />
    <title>SnapApp - Youtube Downloader</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include('layout/navbar') %>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="content">
      <section class="section-one">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="col">
            <div class="section-one-content mt-4">
              <h1 class="section-one-heading">
                SnapApp - Download Your Files Easily
              </h1>
              <p class="section-one-text">
                SnapApp is a user-friendly tool that allows you to download
                files from various sources with ease.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="section-one-form mt-4">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 inputbg">
                  <div class="input-group">
                    <input
                      type="text"
                      class="form-control"
                      id="link_url"
                      placeholder="Input our URL in here..."
                    />
                    <div class="input-group-append">
                      <button class="btn" type="button" id="pasteBtn">
                        <i class="bi bi-clipboard"></i>
                      </button>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-sm-12 mt-3 buttonUnduh">
                  <button
                    id="downloadButton"
                    class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"
                    type="submit"
                  >
                    <i class="bi bi-cloud-download-fill"></i> Download
                  </button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="resultWrapper"></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Section two -->
      <section class="section-two" style="background-color: #3a4f52">
        <div class="headertext">
          <h1 class="judulgede">How to Download with SnapApp</h1>
          <p class="section-two-text">
            Follow these simple steps to download content videos/foto from any
            Sosial media using SnapApp:
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="headtwo" style="width: 100%">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="row row g-0">
              <div class="img col-md-4">
                <img
                  src="../img/Social tree-amico.png"
                  class="img-fluid rounded-start"
                  alt="..."
                />
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-8">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h5 class="card-title">
                    Open the social media platform from which you want to
                    download any content :
                  </h5>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    The first step is to find the link to the content through
                    each platform's respective features. Usually, you can locate
                    the link by using the "share" feature available on the posts
                    or content you want to download.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row row g-0">
              <div class="col-md-8">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h5 class="card-title">
                    Once you have successfully located the link to the content
                    you wish to download, the next step is to return to the
                    Snapapp website :
                  </h5>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    What are the benefits of using our website? You can download
                    content from anywhere you wish simply by pasting the link
                    into the input box above. Currently, we support downloading
                    from 4 social media platforms.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-4">
                <img
                  src="../img/ig.png"
                  class="img-fluid rounded-start"
                  alt="..."
                />
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row row g-0">
              <div class="col-md-4">
                <img
                  src="../img/ig.png"
                  class="img-fluid rounded-start"
                  alt="..."
                />
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-8">
                <div class="card-body">
                  <h5 class="card-title">
                    After successfully entering the link of the content you want
                    to download, just wait for a few moments until the process
                    is completed quickly and efficiently :
                  </h5>
                  <p class="card-text">
                    After the process is completed, you can now download the
                    content and choose your preferred resolution before
                    downloading it to your device. Before downloading any
                    content, please read our terms of service.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- section 3 -->
      <section class="section-faq" id="faq">
        <h2>FAQs</h2>
        <div class="parent">
          <div
            style="
              visibility: hidden;
              position: absolute;
              width: 0px;
              height: 0px;
            "
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <symbol viewBox="0 0 24 24" id="expand-more">
                <path d="M16.59 8.59L12 13.17 7.41 8.59 6 10l6 6 6-6z" />
                <path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none" />
              </symbol>
              <symbol viewBox="0 0 24 24" id="close">
                <path
                  d="M19 6.41L17.59 5 12 10.59 6.41 5 5 6.41 10.59 12 5 17.59 6.41 19 12 13.41 17.59 19 19 17.59 13.41 12z"
                />
                <path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none" />
              </symbol>
            </svg>
          </div>

          <div class="detail-head">
            <details>
              <summary>
                Which social media platforms are supported for downloading on
                SnapApp?
                <svg
                  class="control-icon control-icon-expand"
                  width="24"
                  height="24"
                  role="presentation"
                >
                  <use
                    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                    xlink:href="#expand-more"
                  />
                </svg>
                <svg
                  class="control-icon control-icon-close"
                  width="24"
                  height="24"
                  role="presentation"
                >
                  <use
                    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                    xlink:href="#close"
                  />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <p>
                Currently, we support downloading content from Instagram,
                TikTok, Facebook, and YouTube.
              </p>
            </details>
          </div>
          <details>
            <summary>
              How to download content from YouTube?
              <svg
                class="control-icon control-icon-expand"
                width="24"
                height="24"
                role="presentation"
              >
                <use
                  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                  xlink:href="#expand-more"
                />
              </svg>
              <svg
                class="control-icon control-icon-close"
                width="24"
                height="24"
                role="presentation"
              >
                <use
                  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                  xlink:href="#close"
                />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p>You can find the download button in the three-dot menu at the corner of the video.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>
              Are there any restrictions?
              <svg
                class="control-icon control-icon-expand"
                width="24"
                height="24"
                role="presentation"
              >
                <use
                  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                  xlink:href="#expand-more"
                />
              </svg>
              <svg
                class="control-icon control-icon-close"
                width="24"
                height="24"
                role="presentation"
              >
                <use
                  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
                  xlink:href="#close"
                />
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <p>Only your imagination my friend. Go forth!</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <%- include('layout/footer') %>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/materialize/1.0.0/js/materialize.min.js"></script>
    <script
      src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/crypto-js/4.1.1/crypto-js.min.js"
      integrity="sha512-E8QSvWZ0eCLGk4km3hxSsNmGWbLtSCSUcewDQPQWZF6pEU8GlT8a5fF32wOl1i8ftdMhssTrF/OhyGWwonTcXA=="
      crossorigin="anonymous"
      referrerpolicy="no-referrer"
    ></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/axios/dist/axios.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/sweetalert2@11"></script>
    <script
      src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
      integrity="sha384-geWF76RCwLtnZ8qwWowPQNguL3RmwHVBC9FhGdlKrxdiJJigb/j/68SIy3Te4Bkz"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    ></script>
    <script src="../js/download-page-en.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
